The CSS &quot;Order&quot; property, combined with a media query, can be used to re-order columns when they get stacked in smaller screens.

Something like this:
```
@media only screen and (max-width: 768px) {
    #first {
        order: 2;
    }
    #second {
        order: 4;
    }
    #third {
        order: 1;
    }
    #fourth {
        order: 3;
    }
}
```

