https://github.com/laravel/framework/issues/29978

To work around it you can associate the models manually:

```lang-php
$user = User::find(1);
$sub = Subscription::create([&#39;name&#39; =&gt; &#39;Test Subscription&#39;]);
$user-&gt;subscription()-&gt;associate($sub);
$user-&gt;save();
```

